Careers


IMS Coordinator, NamibiaLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Integrated Management System (IMS) Coordinator, Namibia
Introduction
The purpose of this position is to coordinate the implementation and maintenance of the HSE Management System in conformance with B2Gold requirements at the Otjikoto Gold Mine. 
Location and Reporting Structure
Reporting to the Safety Superintendent, this position will be based at the B2Gold Namibia Otjikoto Mine.
Duties and Responsibilities
Implement and maintain the Health, Safety and Environment Management System 

Monitor and sustain health, safety and environmental risk processes across the facility to eliminate and or reduce risks and impacts
Coordinate the complete gap assessments against defined management system standards with internal parties that includes corrective actions necessary to close identified gaps
Generate HSEM system metrics and report and communicate the status of the management system to HOD/Safety Superintendent and relevant stakeholders
Ensure appropriate follow up on issues that arise out of audits and inspections

Training, Awareness and Education

Plan and co-ordinate the safety training programs to ensure effective safety training for all B2Gold Namibia operations
Identify and analyse HSE training needs across the business unit
Source, compile and update training matrices and material and ensure commitment and adherence from all stakeholders
Ensure continuous improvement with regard to training material and equipment and initiate upgrades to ensure quality and legal compliance
Assist to maintain and improve safety, health and environmental standards and practices
Monitor the effectiveness of the safety and health awareness training programme in areas of responsibility and make recommendations to Head of Departments and Section Heads where required
Ensure that all trainees are assessed in terms of their competency levels prior to and after training, where possible
Ensure that external training providers have updated material and ensure the quality of training and accuracy of information

Administration

Liaise with the HOD/Safety Superintendent to update material and stay abreast of changes
Support line management to ensure that HSE-related transgressions are addressed via updated records on CSafe
Improve and maintain the HSE Management System CSafe database
Participate to write and review the HSE documents and procedures
Prepare internal monthly EHS Reports and statistics
Report all unsafe acts and conditions as well as injuries, accidents, equipment damage and near miss incidents to your supervisor in a timely manner
Ensure prompt action of all corrective actions of investigations, inspections and audits
Conduct hazard identification and risk assessments in work area and ensure records reflect in CSafe accordingly
Ensure prompt action on all safety issues brought up by employees
Maintain a safe working attitude utilising the principles of Duty of Care
Encourage all employees to develop and maintain a safe working attitude utilising the principles of Duty of Care
Complete site and area specific inductions
Inspect work areas weekly and report this in writing to Safety Superintendent
Accountable for the CSafe system in the Safety Department
Coordinate and participate in the departmental safety meetings

Mine Health, Safety and Environmental Effectiveness

Ensure work is carried out safely and in accordance with company procedures
Ensure good housekeeping is maintained at all times
Comply with company safety standards

Compensation and Requirements

Bachelor’s degree, preferably a BS OHS, IMS, or any Engineering course 
Sound knowledge in OHSAS 18001 and or ISO 14001 Management Systems
Certificate of OHS and/or IMS Trainings in Occupational Health, Safety or Environmental Management with at least 5 years’ experience in open pit mining safety & 10 years’ experience in HSE Discipline
Basic Occupational Health & Safety course; Loss Control Management
Trainer's Training
Safety Training Incident Investigation, HSE Representative and Risk Management
Code BE driver’s license

If you are interested and have the required knowledge and skills, you can submit your CV to (minjobnam@b2gold.com). Please indicate the position name in the Subject line.



HSEP Manager, VancouverLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Health, Safety, Environmental, and Permitting Manager
Introduction
The Health, Safety, Environmental, and Permitting Manager will lead the Corporation’s healthy, safety, and environment programs; Track performance, identify priorities and develop strategies and programs to ensure continuous improvement in the Corporation’s health, safety, and environmental performance; Support regional and site staff in all aspects of health, safety, and environmental management such as the identification of best practices, investigation of root causes, assessment of risks, implementation of critical controls, and tracking indicators of performance; Ensure that the health, safety, and environment audit program provides a rigorous review of each site’s ability to manage health, safety, and environment and support sites in actions to address deficiencies and realize continuous improvement opportunities; and Support the Corporation’s reporting on health, safety and environment matters.
Location and Reporting Structure
This position is based in the Vancouver Corporate office, but will be required to travel extensively and reports directly to the Senior Vice President, Operations.
Duties and Responsibilities
To manage the Corporation’s health, safety and environment programs

Oversee the corporate health, safety and environment function including establishing Policies and Standards, establishing Directives and Guidance, setting Objectives and Targets, and developing systems and measures that appropriately assess functional performance;
Ensure critical permits are maintained and complied with by all operations;
Provide input into the development of corporate, regional and site procedures/practices:
	
Standardize procedures/practices across the organization as needed;
Establish and maintain the Corporate Crisis Management Plan and coordinate crisis management exercises;
Ensure the completion of annual Asset Retirement Obligation estimates for B2Gold’s sites; and
Ensure that B2Gold’s tailings storage facilities are inspected annually and that inspection findings are communicated to site and corporate management.


Respond to requests and provide guidance and advice across the Corporation/function;
Provide expertise, guidance, mentoring, development and advisory services to all sites within B2Gold in all disciplines associated with health, safety and environmental management:
	
Assist regional and site personnel in implementing health, safety and environmental programs;
Advise and assist site management in the development of hazard control methods and techniques consistent with B2Gold health, safety and environment requirements;
Oversee the implementation and quality control of competency based training systems at B2Gold sites;
Oversee accident investigation process to ensure an effective root cause analysis system is maintained at each operation.  Collect data, analyze trends and communicate across the organization the common reasons why accidents are occurring, including overseeing the implementation of corrective actions at all B2Gold sites relating to findings from accident/incident investigations for extreme risk events at any B2Gold site; and
Ensure management system software is utilized effectively at B2Gold operating sites, including training site personnel in its use and approving and implementing software modifications/updates.


Oversee accident/incident investigations for fatalities and extreme risk events at B2Gold sites;
Measure, audit and evaluate the health, safety and environment management systems and hazard controls at B2Gold operations for conformance with B2Gold’s health, safety and environment requirements and communicate the results of evaluations to site management and appropriate corporate personnel:
	
Oversee the health, safety and environment standards (Management System Standards and Performance Standards) audit program, including communicating results to site management and appropriate corporate personnel.


Ensure appropriate follow up on issues that arise out of audits, inspections and accident/incident investigations;
Review regional and site health, safety and environment budgets;
Oversee the development of the health, safety and environmental components of the Corporation’s Responsibility Report;
Oversee environmental studies and impact assessments for the Corporation’s development projects;

 To build capacity of the Corporation’s health, safety and environmental staff

Assist as necessary in the search for and recruitment of regional and site health, safety and environment personnel;
Engage and support as needed the development of B2Gold regional and site health, safety and environment personnel;

To advise the management group on corporate health, safety and environment

Produce and deliver monthly health, safety and environment reports on the operational performance of B2Gold sites;
Report on health, safety and environmental performance to the Board of Directors Health, Safety, Environment, Corporate Social Responsibility and Security Committee;
Prepare internal and external health, safety and environment reports or components of reports as required;
Interface as required with stakeholders on health, safety and environmental matters;
Conduct and report on health, safety and environment due diligence on potential acquisitions;
Review best practices and the competitive landscape and recommend continuous improvement efforts in corporate health, safety and environment;
Stay current with technological developments, standards, methods and international best practices related to health, safety and environmental management; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.

Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Healthy, Safety, Environmental, and Permitting Manager in the subject line.

We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.




Financial Accountant, West Africa - MaliLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Location and Reporting Structure
Reporting to the Finance Manager, this position will be based at the B2Gold Mali Fekola Mine.
Introduction
The Financial Accountant is responsible for financial reporting internally and externally to Head Office (Vancouver) taking into consideration the different statutory requirements like IFRS, OHADA and Malian Tax Law. The duties also include assistance with budgets and forecasts; cash flow requirements, liaising with stakeholders to communicate difficult and complex financial transactions; and development of SOX controls. A major initial task will be the development of processes and procedures to move from construction to operations.
Duties and Responsibilities
Financial Reporting
Prepare/compile/generate financial reports including but not limited to:

Monthly and quarterly reports required by Head Office in Vancouver;
Preparation of additional analysis and breakdowns as requested by Head Office in Vancouver;
Monthly and year-end reports required by Malian Tax Law, OHADA and other Malian Statutory requirements;
Oversee and review the maintenance of accounting and other integrated systems;
Develop and implement a plan to change accounting and control practices/procedures from construction phase to operational phase;
Review reconciliations of the group of companies’ trial balances in terms of IFRS, Malian Tax and OHADA requirements;
Provide coaching and guidance related to financial complexities like group accounting policies and IFRS vs OHADA accounting standards as well as development vs. commercial production phase;
Analysis and interpretation of financial data and information and make recommendations;
Assist with preparation and filing of various statutory returns;
Assist with establishment of operational objectives for each financial year with cooperation of key stakeholders
Assist with financial planning and forecasting standards and cash flow requirements
Assist with communication of approved financial plans and forecasts to relevant stakeholders

General Duties

Build and maintain healthy and transparent relationships with stakeholders (internal and external);
Act as an interface between the financial and non - financial stakeholders and provide advice on the interpretation of relevant financial and cost management reports;
Develop and apply mechanisms and structures to ensure adherence to governance practices and protocols (Malian Tax Laws, OHADA, IFRS and other Malian Statutory requirements);
Assist with audit enquiries (external or internal) and special investigations;
Monitor and ensure adherence to SOX compliance for the respective processes responsible for;
Hands-on day to day monitoring and supervising to ensure accurate accounting practices by staff, including coaching and creating opportunities for development; and
Design, develop and implement effective preventative and detective internal audit systems and controls.

Competencies and Requirements

NFQ 8 Qualification in Financial/Management Accounting
Qualified Chartered Accountant
At least 5 years’ post-qualification relevant experience, of which most should have been in the mining industry
ERP system experience

Application Must be Emailed to:
Mali.Recruitment@b2gold.com
Indicate the Vacancy Reference Number: “FEK-Comptable-Financier” in the subject line of your email.
CLOSING DATE: 21 July 2017 
ONLY SHORTLISTED CANDIDATES WILL BE CONTACTED



Regional CSR Manager, VancouverLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Regional Corporate Social Responsibility Manager, Vancouver
Introduction
The Regional CSR Manager will fulfill the mandate of social responsibility mandate for B2Gold. Working closely with senior management at all sites and with field teams, the Regional CSR Manager will mobilize the organization and collaborate in the development of CSR strategies for the Company.
Main duties will be to direct and manage the social and community issues related to B2Gold global projects and operations and to provide reporting to corporate management, as required. The Regional CSR Manager will be a self-directed professional who is comfortable working in a fast-paced environment where there is frequent change. International and domestic travel will be required.
Location and Reporting Structure
Based in the Vancouver Corporate office, this position reports directly to the Senior Vice President, Operations.
Duties and Responsibilities

Fulfill the corporate CSR mandate of: i) social risk management; ii) capability development; and iii) community investment;
Working with the other Regional CSR Manager colleague, provide direction to our sites on the implementation of our social responsibility policy, social performance standards, and community investment strategy;
Define or contribute to CSR strategies at sites related to social issues such as: stakeholder engagement, grievance and conflict management, community investment, artisanal mining, resettlement and land acquisition, human rights, local employment, and sustainability;
Identify, analyze, and manage business risks related to social impacts;
Manage data and information and monitor social performance metrics and indicators;
Provide monthly, quarterly, and annual reports to Corporate management, as required;
Maintain communication with all sites assigned to your responsibility with respect to CSR activities, including community relations teams, mine managers, and country managers;
Travel to all current and future operations and projects of B2Gold, as required;
Supervise and at times, execute training and capacity building for CSR skills and strategy;
Provide guidance for CSR budgets;
Participate in due diligence and assessment of socio-economic settings, risks, and issues related to acquisitions and mergers, as required;
Maintain current on industry best practice and international performance standards related to social issues; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.

Competencies and Requirements

Degree in International Development, Social Science, or a relevant field, preferred;
At least 8 years of relevant experience, preferred;
Experience in the mining industry or extractive sector, preferred;
Experience in managing teams directly and virtually, required;
Strong knowledge, expertise, and understanding of the application and implementation of IFC Performance Standards, required;
International working experience, required;
Demonstrated ability to scale and apply strategies to local environments and different cultures;
Excellent communication and collaboration abilities with all levels of internal employees and external stakeholders;
Ability to work with minimum supervision, manage multi-tasking and multiple demands;
Knowledge and experience working with Microsoft software (Word, Outlook, Excel, Project);
Strong English written, verbal and presentation skills, required; and
Fluency in Spanish and French, as asset;

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.

Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Regional CSR Manager, Vancouver in the subject line.

We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.



Deputy Mining Manager, West Africa – Mali Learn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Deputy Mining Manager, West Africa – Mali 
Introduction
The Deputy Mining Manager will be responsible for managing all open pit operations such as drilling, blasting, and loading and hauling to optimize the use of allocated resources and ensure that the pit production targets are achieved.
Location and Reporting Structure
Reporting to the Mining Manager, this position will be a fly in – fly out rotation, based at the B2Gold Mali Fekola Mine.
Duties and Responsibilities

Plan the activities of the pit to produce the short, medium, and long term required production targets to achieve optimal efficiencies;
Investigate and recommend final pit design parameters and surface layouts to the Mining Manager;
Liaise with the maintenance team on the scheduling of maintenance of the earthmoving fleet;
Implement and coordinate continuous improvement initiatives which target efficiency for the pit operation and productivity improvements;
Management of pit operation on ensuring continuous supply of feed ore to the processing plant;
Management of any possible Contractors in the pit to ensure production and adherence to safety procedures, and relevant statutory legislation;
Continuously analyze processes and systems in the pit with a view of finding ways for corrective action that could eliminate problem areas and to re-align again with set goals and objectives;
Plan, schedule, and resource to meet set targets of the pit;
Facilitate the morning daily production meeting, document, and ensure a controlled filing system of all proceedings;
Draw up annual budget for pit operation for approval by the Mining Manager;
Manage the daily operational performance of subordinates to ensure adherence to production targets;
Identify training needs of the section and liaise with relevant parties to achieve development goals;
Establish and maintain sound working relationships with co-workers/team members to resolve problems;
Ensure work is done safely and in accordance with company procedures;
Ensure good housekeeping is maintained in all areas of operation;
Comply with company safety standards; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.

Competencies and Requirements

A Degree or High National Diploma in Mining Engineering;
At least 8-10 years mining experience in surface mining operations;
Knowledge of explosive and Minerals Act and Regulations;
Hot and dusty work environment experience required;
Possession of Code BE driver’s license; and
Valid open pit blasting ticket.

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.

Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Deputy Mining Manager, West Africa – Mali in the subject line.

We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.



Senior Mining Engineer, West Africa – Mali Learn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Senior Mining Engineer, West Africa – Mali 
Introduction
The Senior Mining Engineer is responsible for providing mine planning services within the mining engineering group, including scheduling, drilling layouts, blasting assistance, coordination with grade control, and other general requirements of mining operations of a producing gold mine. He/she ensures the mining operations section meets the needs of an expanding operation while maintaining an international standard of practice and a high level of internal communications.
This position will be responsible for long-term mine planning for the open pit mine and delivering production data and reports, stockpile accounting, and mine-mill reconciliation. Emphasis will be on minimizing dilution and ore loss, training and mentoring, tracking ore stockpile quantities and quality, and maintaining high standards of work safety and health.
Location and Reporting Structure
Reporting to the Technical Services Manager, this position will be a fly in – fly out rotation, based at the B2Gold Mali Fekola Mine.
Duties and Responsibilities

Adhere to and support all company related policies and procedures;
Prepare long-term mine plans to ensure site alignment with yearly budget;
Optimize the extraction of mineralized zones and minimize dilution;
Understand, monitor, and develop geotechnical site requirements;
Optimize pit and dump designs using geotechnical design parameters and pit phasing;
Plan for water management of in-pit water;
Assist with strategic mine planning and development of assumptions and schedules for quarterly forecasts and yearly budgets;
Assist in identifying efficiency gains and cost savings;
Assist in training and developing junior national engineers and other technical services staff;
Liaise with Load and Haul on a daily basis to ensure minimal ore loss and dilution;
Assure safe working practices and environment, cooperate with other departments in safety programs;
Ensure timely preparation of daily and weekly mine plans to ensure alignment with three month rolling plans;
Prepare clearly written monthly reports and other documentation on required frequencies;
Maintain constructive and effective working relationships with B2Gold employees, contractors, and consultants; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.

Competencies and Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Mining Engineering or an equivalent;
Minimum 8 years’ experience;
Minimum of 5 years’ experience at producing gold mines;
Proficient with Microsoft office products and at least one mining software package, preferably Surpac;
Experience with workplace safety programs; and
Possession of Code B drivers’ license.

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.

Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Senior Mining Engineer, West Africa – Mali in the subject line.

We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.



Accounts Payable Clerk, VancouverLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso. This position will work with B2Gold Logistics Corp. which is a wholly-owned subsidiary of B2Gold Corp. B2Gold Logistics provides support for offshore purchasing and logistic services for B2Gold group projects.
Position
Accounts Payable Clerk
Location and Reporting Structure
Based in the Vancouver Corporate office, this position reports directly to the Corporate Accountant.
Duties and Responsibilities

Receive and stamp invoices;
Perform invoice verification for accounts payable related documentation (three-way matching between invoice, receipt note, and purchase order);
Record relevant account details on invoice;
Obtain coding and approvals for all AP invoices;
Process invoice in Sage X3 with relevant approvals;
Display document and investigate blocked invoices;
Resolve blocking reasons and unblock invoice or escalate;
Reconcile vendor statements on monthly basis and before each payment;
Handle vendor queries;
Identify invoices to be paid and prepare payment request;
Prepare monthly intercompany invoices to subsidiaries;
Prepare quarterly accrual list;
Prepare bank reconciliations;
Assist with month end;
File, photocopy, scan, and general office duties, as required; and
Other duties as set out by the Company.

Competencies and Requirements

Sage X3 experience is an asset;
3 years’ full cycle AP experience:
	
Multi-currency;
Project costing;
Matching and capturing invoices in an ERP system;


Intermediate Microsoft Office skills;
Effective written and verbal communication skills;
Excellent attention to detail; and
Be able to build excellent relationships with vendors and team members.

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.
Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Accounts Payable Clerk in the subject line.
We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.



Pit Foreman, West Africa – MaliLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Pit Foreman, West Africa – Mali 
Introduction
The Pit Foreman will be responsible for coordinating, monitoring, and supervising mining operations (drilling, loading, and hauling). He/she will ensure optimal and effective usage of mining resources to achieve optimal production in accordance with mine plan priorities and uphold the Company safety standards.
Location and reporting structure
Reporting to the Pit Superintendent, this position will be a fly in – fly out rotation, based at the B2Gold Mali Fekola Mine.
Duties and responsibilities

Plan, coordinate, and direct mine production/operation activities including drilling sequencing and loading and hauling to ensure a safe, productive, high quality, low cost, and efficient operation;
Monitor adherence to operation procedures;
Take corrective actions where deficiencies are observed;
Ensure adherence to short term plans as designed by Mining Engineers;
Determine resource availability and plan stock levels to avoid downtime;
Ensure messages/requests are conveyed clearly and understood by recipients;
Use correct line and channel of communication;
Supervise the daily operational performance of subordinates to ensure adherence to production targets;
Plan and draw up task allocations for the subordinates and ensure availability of required resources;
Monitor and control labour resources by taking disciplinary measures in cases of deviations and rewarding good performance;
Identify training needs of the section and liaise with relevant parties to achieve development goals;
Initiate on-the-job training where required;
Supervise operational compliance of subordinates and in relation to equipment utilization and skill levels;
Take corrective actions in case of abuse or negligent operation or damage to equipment;
Attend meetings and convey messages to subordinates;
Ensure work is done safely and in accordance with company procedures;
Ensure good housekeeping is maintained in all areas of operation;
Comply with company safety standards; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.

Competencies and Requirements

Minimum educational qualification: Grade 12;
At least 10 years mining experience in surface mining operations of which 5 years must be on mining supervisory level;
Knowledge of explosive and Minerals Act and Regulations;
Possession of Code BE driver’s license;
Valid open pit blasting ticket; and
Supervisory certificate is an asset.

Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus full benefit package for employee and dependents.
Please apply by emailing your resume with a short introduction including your salary expectations to jobs@b2gold.com, and state Pit Foreman, West Africa – Mali in the subject line.
We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp.; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.



Pit Superintendent, West Africa – MaliLearn More

The Company
Headquartered in Vancouver, Canada, B2Gold Corp. (“B2Gold”) is one of the fastest-growing intermediate gold producers in the world. Founded in 2007, B2Gold has evolved into an international gold mining company, with four operating mines, one mine under construction and numerous exploration projects across four continents in various countries, including Nicaragua, the Philippines, Namibia, Mali and Burkina Faso.
Position
Pit Superintendent, West Africa – Mali 
Introduction
The Pit Superintendent will be responsible for managing the pit operations such as drilling, blasting, and loading and hauling to optimize the use of allocated resources and ensure that the pit production targets are achieved.
Location and reporting structure
Reporting to the Mining Manager, this position will be a fly in – fly out rotation, based at the B2Gold Mali Fekola Mine.
Duties and responsibilities

Plan the activities of the pit to produce the short, medium, and long term required production targets to achieve optimal efficiencies;
Investigate and recommend final pit design parameters and surface layouts to the Mining Manager;
Liaise with the maintenance team on the scheduling of maintenance of the earthmoving fleet;
Implement and coordinate continuous improvement initiatives which target efficiency for the pit operation and productivity improvements;
Management of pit operation on ensuring continuous supply of feed ore to the processing plant;
Management of any possible Contractors in the pit to ensure production and adherence to safety procedures, and relevant statutory legislation;
Continuously analyze processes and systems in the pit with a view of finding ways for corrective action that could eliminate problem areas and to realign again with set goals and objectives;
