BTG shares fall as revenue outlook fails to please
(Updates with more detail, share price, analyst comment) LONDON--Shares in BTG PLC (BTG.LN) fell as much as 11% Tuesday after the company reported lower annual pretax profit and dissapointed analysts on its revenue outlook. The drug group said pretax profit in the year ended March 31 was 31.6 million pounds ($40.8 million) compared with GBP57.5 million a year earlier.

May. 16, 2017 at 10:43 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









BTG profit falls even as use of Varithena rises
LONDON--BTG PLC (BTG.LN) on Tuesday reported lower annual pretax profit, though it noted a steady increase in demand for its varicose vein treatment, Varithena. The drug group said pretax profit in the year ended March 31 was 31.6 million pounds ($40.8 million) compared with GBP57.5 million a year earlier, while revenue rose 11% to GBP570.5 million from GBP447.5 million.

May. 16, 2017 at 3:07 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









